  "prompt": "How can I know if I'm not pregnant without using a test?",
  "response": "While a pregnancy test is the most reliable method to confirm pregnancy, some early signs and symptoms may indicate pregnancy:\n\n1. Missed period\n2. Nausea or morning sickness\n3. Breast tenderness or swelling\n4. Fatigue\n5. Frequent urination\n6. Food cravings or aversions\n7. Mood swings\n8. Light spotting or cramping\n\nHowever, these symptoms can also be caused by other factors. The only way to know for certain is to:\n- Take a home pregnancy test\n- Visit a healthcare provider\n- Get a blood test\n\nFor the most accurate results, wait until after a missed period and use a pregnancy test.",
